author: greg_duncan
title: fantastic!
review: keetongu rocks.although shorter than the other titans,he makes up for it with his colour,his parts,and features,especially the spinner.one cool part about this set is that it includes a little piece which lets you attach the cord to his back,it looks like an antenna.only one thing bothered me about this set.he doesnt look like an animal,but like a very cool robot i love already!

author: Laura_Jerbi
title: Weird, says mom,,,,son says awesome!!
review:
My 10 year old and I put this together.  A bit complicated, and the creature seems to be a bit woobly.   Leave it to a 10 year old to figure out how to expose the spinner. 
As a mom, I am overwhelmed with the range of the Bionicle line.   Cheap sets to awfully price-y, but the "play-ability" will keep my buying them for my son.

author: KLOKRIECHER
title: LEGO BIONICLE (Warriors) - Keetongu Review
review:
This is a fun set to have and it's fun to play with as well.

Box/Instructions

The instruction has 48 pages and there're no mistakes in it.

Parts

This set has a lot of useful pieces which are always great to have for future MOC's (My Own Creations) and/or brickfilms for sure. The bags are numbered.

The build

The build is very nice and easy and we also don't get any stickers to worry about.

The completed model

[img]http://www.klokriecher.de/gallery_pics/l/8755-1.jpg[/img]


The legs, the feet, the arms, the hands and the head can be adjusted. On one hand we can see a double-sided shield which sviwels full 360°. The other hand has a sword. On the body is a piece which you can fold down if you want to use the spinner which flies very well. I really like the orange color on him as well. The only thing I don't like that this guy falls down very easily, too. I depends on the position of the legs.

Summary

All in all this set is an great set and I would HIGHLY recommend you to get this. You can find this set on eBay, BrickLink and Amazon for sure. Here is the link where you can check out the full gallery I made for this set on my website: http://www.klokriecher.de

Stopmotion

author: reidak12
title: Unique Rahi
review:
Hi again! It's been a long time since my last review, so I'm a bit out of practice. I'm aware that Bionicle has been out of production for two years now, but that does not detract from them at all. They are still amazing toys. I got the Voporak set on Amazon, and since I think that model is hideous, I built the three figures instead. Keetongu is an unusual figure, as he is as far as I know, the only rahi (animal), that appears to be an ordinary figure. There are some terrific features present.

Pros
good color
some rarer pieces
sturdy
slightly but not overly technic build
rotating shield works well
finally a red spinner!
I like how the rip cord is stowed on his back, and not stupid looking like on other models
although there is no head persay, it doesn't look awful
flip out chest is very cool and unique

Cons
too short
blade on right arm is kind of stupid looking (however it is a good size)

All in all, this is a very well designed set. If you are a Bionicle collector, I would recommend getting it if you can find a good price on ebay or anywhere.

author: tkettle9719
title: The Hero among Rahi.
review:
I got this set for myself many years ago, and think that it is really great Bionicle individual for anyone's collection.

Pros

  • -The yellow, black, and gray prove to be an excellent combo.
  • This guy has a unique Rhotuka location, and an excellent spin mesh blade.
  • …

Cons

  • -The arms are a bit unmotivated to me.
  • I also wish that the head would be a bit more solid.
  • …

This set is a great large Bionicle to add to your collection, and has a nice solid design. I highly recommend this guy.
